 I just go to random spot in such and such a zone to find folks that do roleplay.  I just roleplay my character the way I always have, with anybody I run into that wants to listen to me babble. Heh.  I rarely go OOC, and I hold fast to my principles, and refuse to help evil characters out.<br>
<br>
I find that people will roleplay if they are roleplayed to.  This tends to be true even in the high-end game; we have a great collection of people here on both sides that will uphold RP standards.  On the other hand, I've been here for a very long time, and I never have to join a random pickup group with characters I shouldn't really be associating with.  I am blessed to have a great guild and the Fellowship to group with, and all of them stick to their principles, even in the 50s, and it's a nice thing.  But I imagine it might be hard to create a new character here tomorrow and expect things to work out as well as they have for Elsie.<br>
<br>
EQ just has too many things about it that are not conducive to a roleplay mindset, and VI/SOE changing so many of our rules on March 8th didn't help with that.  But I am glad I came here, and I have been lucky. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jharycleric>Jharycleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 12:24:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1941.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Work with the Roleplay</span><hr size=1> Mainly I was concerned with just giving the peoples I mentioned a chance to roleplay with you.  If a Wood Elf tries to tell Shin how evil they are, Shin can be dismissive, try and duel them, insult their mother, but Shin will give the person a shot at roleplaying. As I metioned, I have had some fun with the Ven Sho, they are nothing but dismissive, and derisive, they are also really cool people some of whom I have had the pleasure of raiding with in OOC fashion. I know some people have talked crap about that too, but as Fuvi mentioned once, till you try and play in an All or mostly Iksar Guild you have no idea the true high end limitations placed upon you by the game. Sometimes you just want to try stuff out, or see places and things ya wouldn't have otherwise. <br>
